WEBVTT

00:04.226 --> 00:05.087
Welcome to Life Church.

00:05.488 --> 00:07.832
We're here to help you become who God created you to be.

00:08.012 --> 00:09.094
And we'd love to hear from you.

00:09.635 --> 00:15.604
Take a quick survey at life.church slash podcast connect to let us know how we can support you on your faith journey.

00:15.965 --> 00:17.307
And now let's go to the message.

00:22.576 --> 00:27.083
So when it hit me, it hit really, really hard.

00:28.485 --> 00:31.570
And I didn't see it coming.

00:33.602 --> 00:34.743
I don't think anybody did.

00:35.965 --> 00:39.470
I was preaching every weekend just like normal.

00:40.491 --> 00:46.278
My marriage to Amy by the grace of God has always been good and we were in a very, very good place.

00:47.320 --> 00:53.367
Physically, I was healthy, eating goods, sleeping okay, exercising and such.

00:54.429 --> 01:01.618
All exterior signs seem normal, but I had been ignoring my soul.

01:02.818 --> 01:05.883
And my mind was paying the price.

01:07.586 --> 01:12.173
The first thing that I noticed was a shortness of breath.

01:13.215 --> 01:15.498
And I'd never really experienced that before.

01:15.538 --> 01:24.172
And then there was this mental fog followed by like sheer panic.

01:26.155 --> 01:28.038
And I was in a place that I'd never been before.

01:28.118 --> 01:30.482
I needed help.

01:31.650 --> 01:32.832
And I didn't know how to ask for it.

01:34.274 --> 01:38.419
Because not only am I a Christian, but I'm the pastor, right?

01:39.220 --> 01:41.183
I'm supposed to be the one that's helping others.

01:42.204 --> 01:44.948
I'm not supposed to be the one that's struggling and falling apart.

01:45.549 --> 01:49.634
And unfortunately, some of you may be able to relate.

01:50.576 --> 01:53.660
Sadly, tragically, there are a lot of people today that can relate.

01:54.661 --> 01:57.245
Outwardly, you may look really, really normal.

01:58.246 --> 02:01.330
But inwardly, you might be battling with anxiety.

02:02.114 --> 02:05.981
and stress or exhaustion and depression.

02:07.543 --> 02:11.290
If you're there, I want to tell you right now, you are not alone.

02:12.291 --> 02:13.593
Our Heavenly Father is here.

02:13.654 --> 02:18.963
He understands your pain and he wants to bring healing for your hurting mind.

02:20.185 --> 02:21.988
If you're hurting today, would you join me in praying?

02:22.048 --> 02:25.714
Father, we thank you for your goodness, for your grace, for your power, for your presence.

02:26.306 --> 02:34.395
and God that we ask by the preaching of your word, by the power of your Holy Spirit, and by whatever means you choose, would you do a work in us today?

02:35.916 --> 02:41.442
Heal us that we can be your grace and love for those who need healing as well.

02:41.503 --> 02:42.083
We pray this.

02:42.664 --> 02:46.648
In the name of Jesus and all God's people said, amen, amen.

02:47.369 --> 02:55.698
Today we are starting a new message series that's called Heal Your Hurting Mind based on a book that is coming out this week, Heal Your Hurting Mind,

02:55.842 --> 03:02.710
subtitle is biblical hope for anxiety, depression, burnout, and the emotions that no one talks about.

03:02.750 --> 03:13.582
The reason that I wrote this book is because it seems like more and more people, even Christians today, are feeling this ongoing inward tension.

03:14.443 --> 03:15.244
Maybe you can relate.

03:16.105 --> 03:24.434
There are some of you, you know you've been saved by the grace of Jesus, born anew, and yet you're still struggling emotionally.

03:25.250 --> 03:31.336
Others of you, you have a real genuine faith in God, and you still battle with fear.

03:32.497 --> 03:41.986
Some of you, you know you love God, and you do love God, and you need God, and you call on God, and you're in His Word, and yet your mind just won't stop racing.

03:43.468 --> 03:49.673
Some of the tension that you feel, I want to tell you right now, it does not mean that you're failing spiritually.

03:50.674 --> 03:54.418
In many cases, I think, is that we don't truly understand

03:54.498 --> 04:06.416
how it is that our good God designed us and made us, and if we don't understand how we're designed, we're likely to misdiagnose the problem, which is exactly what I was doing.

04:07.137 --> 04:15.429
And what I want to do is I want to show you in God's word what he says about how you are made and what he wants to do in you.

04:16.110 --> 04:24.082
Paul said, it's recorded in 1 Thessalonians 5, verse 23, he said this, may God himself,

04:24.866 --> 04:26.147
What kind of God is he?

04:26.688 --> 04:29.031
The God of peace.

04:29.952 --> 04:35.378
May God himself, the God of peace, sanctify you through and through.

04:35.398 --> 04:37.921
What does it mean to be sanctified?

04:38.382 --> 04:41.565
Well, when you're forgiven by Jesus, you're justified.

04:41.626 --> 04:43.408
That means your sins are forgiven.

04:44.088 --> 04:47.192
The theology term is like, it's just as if I'd never sinned.

04:47.352 --> 04:48.213
You're made new.

04:48.433 --> 04:49.314
You're justified.

04:49.435 --> 04:52.338
Sanctification, though, is the process

04:52.450 --> 04:56.014
over time where the Holy Spirit starts to renew you.

04:56.034 --> 04:59.739
You're not just say, but you're becoming like Jesus.

05:00.160 --> 05:06.968
Paul says, may God himself, the God of peace, sanctify you, how through and through.

05:07.048 --> 05:15.058
May your whole, then watch what he says, spirit, soul, and body be kept blameless.

05:15.362 --> 05:19.686
Remember our God is a triune God, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

05:19.946 --> 05:21.708
He created us in His image.

05:21.948 --> 05:26.252
We are triune beings, spirit, soul, and body.

05:26.272 --> 05:29.335
May the God of peace sanctify you through and through.

05:29.355 --> 05:38.484
May your whole spirit, soul, and body be kept blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.

05:39.185 --> 05:44.530
The one who calls you is faithful and he will

05:44.994 --> 05:45.375
Do it.

05:46.216 --> 05:48.839
May the God of peace sanctify you.

05:49.220 --> 05:52.685
He is faithful and he will do it.

05:53.005 --> 05:55.208
I love what God's word says is that he is faithful.

05:55.268 --> 05:56.510
He is true to his word.

05:56.730 --> 05:58.192
He will do what he promised.

05:58.212 --> 05:59.895
What does he want to do in you?

06:00.195 --> 06:01.858
He wants to sanctify you.

06:01.898 --> 06:03.420
He wants to heal you.

06:03.640 --> 06:05.442
He wants to make you like Jesus.

06:05.783 --> 06:09.088
Spirit, soul, and body.

06:10.810 --> 06:11.591
So what are you?

06:12.693 --> 06:13.714
You're not just a body.

06:14.722 --> 06:15.703
You're not just a body.

06:16.244 --> 06:18.367
You may say, well, I'm a body with a soul.

06:18.848 --> 06:21.112
No, you're not just a body with a soul.

06:21.713 --> 06:29.084
What you are is you are a spirit who has a soul that lives in a body.

06:30.726 --> 06:33.050
Sounds like a riddle is hard to remember.

06:33.110 --> 06:33.831
What are you?

06:34.251 --> 06:35.694
You are a spirit.

06:35.734 --> 06:41.362
You're a spiritual being that has a soul that's your mind, your will,

06:41.538 --> 06:48.224
and your emotions, your spiritual being that has a mind, a will, an emotion that lives inside of a body.

06:49.265 --> 06:51.868
Now, what happened years ago?

06:51.908 --> 06:58.434
Well, if you don't have Christ in your life, you may be spiritual, but you're spiritually dead.

06:59.054 --> 07:06.121
If you go back to the garden with Adam and Eve, do you remember what God said about eating from the forbidden fruit?

07:06.161 --> 07:08.623
God said, if you eat of that fruit, what's gonna happen?

07:08.643 --> 07:09.424
Does anybody remember?

07:09.444 --> 07:11.506
He said, you'll surely die.

07:11.714 --> 07:12.655
Did they eat the fruit?

07:13.236 --> 07:14.959
Did they die physically?

07:15.499 --> 07:16.561
They didn't die physically.

07:16.581 --> 07:17.062
What happened?

07:17.402 --> 07:19.245
They died spiritually.

07:19.785 --> 07:23.591
If you eat the fruit, you'll surely die spiritually.

07:24.152 --> 07:25.293
So what are we?

07:25.313 --> 07:27.476
We're a spiritual being with a soul.

07:27.536 --> 07:29.740
And when you receive Christ, what happens?

07:30.080 --> 07:33.685
You are spiritually born again.

07:33.725 --> 07:35.648
You're spiritually born.

07:35.668 --> 07:37.410
You receive eternal life.

07:37.491 --> 07:39.954
So you're a spiritual being with the soul.

07:40.034 --> 07:48.405
Mind, will, and emotions, you are a spiritual being that lives inside of a body that has the soul and with Christ you come alive.

07:48.705 --> 07:52.530
We have to understand what we are so that we'll understand how God heals us.

07:52.650 --> 07:59.239
And what started to happen to me is I learned when I was breaking down that I didn't have a spiritual problem.

07:59.939 --> 08:01.381
I was close to God, I was praying.

08:02.002 --> 08:04.545
I didn't have a physical problem, I was in good shape.

08:04.585 --> 08:08.210
What I had was a soul problem.

08:08.738 --> 08:16.188
My mind was anxious, my emotions were overloaded, and my inner world needed healing.

08:17.009 --> 08:21.616
And here's the challenge when it comes to Christians and mental health.

08:21.636 --> 08:25.781
Sometimes we get weird in the church when it comes to mental health.

08:26.763 --> 08:29.607
Do you know sometimes Christians can be weird?

08:29.627 --> 08:31.549
Sometimes good weird, like you're supposed to be different.

08:31.790 --> 08:34.994
Other times just weird weird, like the wrong kind of weird.

08:35.074 --> 08:45.746
And what happens is sometimes in this area, we tend to think when you get saved, you're justified, you're no longer, when you get saved, then Jesus fixes everything.

08:45.786 --> 08:48.849
And you're supposed to be fine with no problems at all.

08:49.610 --> 08:51.933
This is simply not true.

08:52.533 --> 08:54.135
When Jesus saves you, what does he do?

08:54.536 --> 08:56.157
He makes you spiritually alive.

08:56.658 --> 08:57.799
You're spiritually new.

08:57.839 --> 08:59.721
Your sins are forgiven.

09:00.062 --> 09:02.104
You're a new creation in Christ Jesus.

09:02.124 --> 09:03.986
You're born again.

09:04.322 --> 09:09.127
Spiritually, you're new, but your body doesn't change.

09:10.309 --> 09:13.512
I've never heard anyone that says, like, I called on Jesus.

09:13.872 --> 09:17.777
He forgave my sins and, dang, I've got a six-pack abs now.

09:18.097 --> 09:18.818
Where'd that come from?

09:18.858 --> 09:20.620
It's a miracle.

09:20.660 --> 09:24.504
I called on Jesus and my thighs got thinner and my hair got thicker.

09:24.724 --> 09:25.685
Glory to God.

09:25.705 --> 09:28.008
It doesn't happen that way.

09:28.048 --> 09:33.554
You're saved spiritually, but your body doesn't change and the same is true.

09:33.698 --> 09:37.423
with your mind, your will, and your emotions.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.285
So let's say it this way.

09:39.866 --> 09:40.747
What is salvation?

09:41.227 --> 09:47.295
Salvation is instant, but sanctification takes time.

09:48.256 --> 09:54.424
May the God of peace sanctify you, body, soul, and spirit.

09:55.045 --> 09:58.369
So the great news is we celebrate it in baptism today.

09:58.909 --> 10:00.031
Your sins are forgiven.

10:00.531 --> 10:02.674
You can be saved in a moment

10:02.914 --> 10:07.021
when you call on the name of the risen Christ.

10:07.041 --> 10:08.543
But healing is often a process.

10:09.685 --> 10:19.801
In other words, your spirit can be saved immediately, but your mind, your will, and your emotions, that's actually renewed or sanctified over time.

10:20.342 --> 10:22.225
That's why Paul said this in Romans 12, too.

10:22.245 --> 10:30.578
He said, hey, do not be conformed to the pattern of this world, but be transformed, be changed,

10:30.754 --> 10:34.938
Be made more like Jesus, by the renewing of your mind.

10:35.699 --> 10:45.869
In other words, you can genuinely be a child of God, you're saved by Jesus, you love Jesus, but your mind still needs healing.

10:47.150 --> 10:55.157
You can say all day long, yes, Jesus forgave my sins and made me new, but you still might find yourself battling with anxiety.

10:56.038 --> 10:59.922
Or you can be filled with the spirit of God and yet still fight

11:00.066 --> 11:01.228
against depression.

11:02.389 --> 11:04.352
What do we do with that in the church?

11:05.433 --> 11:08.598
I'm gonna tell you right now, the church should be the safest place to talk about these issues.

11:09.419 --> 11:11.682
The church, I'm gonna say it again because you didn't say an amen back.

11:11.702 --> 11:19.193
The church should be the safest place to talk about these issues and to struggle with mental health issues.

11:19.273 --> 11:21.957
It doesn't make you a bad Christian, it just makes you human.

11:23.198 --> 11:23.819
It makes you human.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.763
And so I wanted to speak directly to you right now.

11:26.943 --> 11:28.786
If you're in the middle of a difficult,

11:28.930 --> 11:30.292
place for whatever reason.

11:31.413 --> 11:34.096
That is not necessarily the sign of weak faith.

11:34.897 --> 11:36.539
It doesn't make you a spiritual failure.

11:37.280 --> 11:44.829
It's very likely a signal that a part of you, spirit, soul, and body needs healing.

11:45.590 --> 11:49.095
And the good news is, you may have been saved, but God's still not finished with you.

11:49.755 --> 11:51.137
God is still working in you.

11:51.558 --> 11:52.519
God is for you.

11:52.559 --> 11:58.386
And He's working in all things to bring about good to those who love Him and are called according to His

11:59.042 --> 12:00.925
purpose.

12:00.945 --> 12:03.588
So we're talking about mental health, excuse me.

12:04.229 --> 12:07.573
And what do we mean when we talk about mental health?

12:08.355 --> 12:10.197
Well, it's holistic.

12:10.257 --> 12:18.448
It includes your emotional, your psychological, your social well-being.

12:19.389 --> 12:23.956
When we talk about your mind or talk about your soul, we're talking about your inner world.

12:24.016 --> 12:25.778
It's how you think, how you

12:25.858 --> 12:44.727
handle pressure, how you respond whenever life wax you upside the head, and you said, I didn't see that coming, and I didn't think she would do that, and I didn't think I would be here, and I didn't think I would be battling with this issue, and I didn't think I'd be alone, and I didn't think I would be so angry, and I didn't think that they were wrong me like that, what am I supposed to do now?

12:44.767 --> 12:47.031
Mental health impacts everything.

12:48.012 --> 12:54.322
Your relationships, your decisions, your attitude, your energy, your faith,

12:55.138 --> 12:59.806
And when we look around today, we see a lot of people battling with mental health issues.

13:00.527 --> 13:00.808
Why?

13:00.848 --> 13:11.326
Well, we can dice it all the different ways because of the different pressures and because of social media and because of all the news that we see and because of all the different challenges and the list could go on and on and on.

13:12.188 --> 13:18.799
Just because they're common today and they are doesn't mean that we didn't see mentally challenging situations in the Bible.

13:19.701 --> 13:20.562
We see it all over.

13:20.962 --> 13:22.163
if you look with eyes to see.

13:22.284 --> 13:29.612
You can look at some of the great, some of the people that we talk about, some of the people, if you were in Sunday school, you had a little flannel board guy of them in Sunday school.

13:29.792 --> 13:31.875
You look at Elijah, remember Elijah?

13:32.516 --> 13:36.260
He's the guy that raised the dead and called fire from heaven.

13:36.320 --> 13:41.827
And at one point said, I'm so depressed, I don't even want to live anymore.

13:42.668 --> 13:48.114
There's David, the Psalms, the guy who's known as a man after God's own heart.

13:48.642 --> 13:51.366
He cries out to God and said, why have you forgotten me God?

13:52.387 --> 13:55.452
Why have you turned your face away from me?

13:56.573 --> 13:58.115
